## JavaScript:
Requires jQuery. Works with 1.4. Also tested in 1.3.2.


## HTML:
Expects label and field pair to have a wrapper element with a class of "inline label":

    <div class="inline_label">
      <label for="email">Email Address</label>
      <input id="email">
    </div>


## CSS:
    .inline_label { position : relative; }

    .inline_label .inline,
    .inline_label .inline.inline_example {
      position  : absolute;
      top       : 6px;
      left      : 4px;
      color     : #555;
      font-size : 12px;
    }

    .inline_label .inline_example.inline {
      // this will require some tweaking
      // depends on margin/padding/font-size
      top : 20px;
    }

    .inline_label .inline.entering_text  { color:   #aaa; }
    .inline_label .inline.value_entered  { display: none !important; }


--------------

## You can also put help text over the input and keep the normal label:

    <div class="inline_label">
      <label for="date">Date</label>
      <span class="inline_example">mm/dd/yyyy</span>
      <input id="date">
    </div>
